1 (b) The data derived from the evaluation of outcomes of services required under
2 subsection (a)(3) of this section shall be:
3 (1) Collected, analyzed, and publicly reported [at least annually] ON OR
4 BEFORE DECEMBER 1 EACH YEAR, BEGINNING IN 2026;
5 (2) Disaggregated by race, gender, age, and zip code; and
6 (3) Used to formulate policy recommendations with the goal of decreasing
7 criminal detention and improving crisis diversion programs and linkages to effective
8 community health services.
9 (c) The Crisis Response System services shall be implemented as determined by
10 the Administration in collaboration with the core service agency or local behavioral health
11 authority serving each jurisdiction and community members of each jurisdiction.
12 (d) An advance directive for mental health services under § 5–602.1 of this article
13 shall apply to the delivery of services under this subtitle.
14 (e) This subtitle may not be construed to affect petitions for emergency
15 evaluations under § 10–622 of this title.
